The Cantica. A Roman comedy consisted of Diverbia (dialogues) and Cantica (monologues, more or less lyrical), chanted or recited to musical accompaniment by a single actor. The metres of the Cantica present the greatest difficulty to the critic. Our state of knowledge respecting their metres1 is perhaps something like what the knowledge of Greek choral metres was in the days of Brunck 3 and with much less prospect of reaching accurate knowledge respect-ing their structure than has been the case with the Greek metres.
